ild to become married.  It made for a great story with a somewhat happy end (or is it a happy end? Muhahahaha).<br><br>I have seen some RL married couples get married in game, I have seen folks get married because they met a great person online and the romance extended into RL. I have seen some get married for the Role Play value or even for the fun of it.<br><br>I think it is a dangerous thing...to let too many of your feeling to get tied up into this game. I have a great love for Mith Marr and for my fellow guildees and lot of the community, but I have a lot of contempt for a great many asses (who's names I never bothered to remember)<br><br>All in all, what do you think about EQ marriages? Would you feel angered if you found out that your spouse was not the opposite sex? Would you even care? Do you marry over love, for story, for both (like me :) ), or would oyu not marry at all? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF7D6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ulorelan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorelan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elf Butt Aficionado<br>MMDN CSC Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 592<br> <font color=#6C8361>(4/9/02 1:03:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xanadu2.net/lorelan/flag.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ Marriages</span><hr size=1> You got married, and I wasn't invited to the wedding?  *sniff*  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Bad ol' stinky inky.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>L <p><CENTER><img src="http://www.xanadu2.n