on you're talking to is unless you have met him or her in person. The opportunities for deception are numerous, and it is easy to do so.<br>Anyone who marries in EQ and does it because he or she is interested in a real life relationship with a person should keep this in mind. Yes, there probably have been quite a few online flirtations turned romances that have busted up people's other relationships. But does this mean that marriage in EQ is bad and should be removed?<br>If you got fooled in EQ, well, get a divorce and move on. I would imagine a lot of the anger here may come from a kind of homophobia. &quot;Oh, no, I had feelings for a girl who was really a guy?! Does that make me gay???&quot; It's an interesting question. If anything, it suggests to me that some of the generalizations that people make about the differences between men and women are overrated. I mean, we've already started to come together on the Farting Issue. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8Dc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/utallia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tallia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#6C8361>(4/12/02 8:31:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ Marriages</span><hr size=1> Was married ingame once in another game. It was roleplay based and we had fun and remain friends online, he plays EQ too, we still hook up  and hunt together on ocassion.  <br><br>As for being married in EQ,  well,  I've declined  several proposals on the basis of how I play my character and marriage for her would not suit her.  <br><br>If you do it for fun/roleplay  thats great.   I've seen too many friends end up hating each other after the ingame thing went sour.  <br><br>Looking for love online.. I dont know about that I never have.  But if you did and found it.. super.<br><br>I think it should be left up to the two folks involved personally.  <br><br>Oh and I always wear my black armor to ingame weddings... seems appropriate  =P <p><p><a href="mailto:talmahera_@excite.com">Tallia Windwalker</a><br>Mystic of Halas <br><a href="http://hammer.prohosting.com/~blkhand">Tal`mahe`Ra</a> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF7D6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukalynntaranis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalynn Taranis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://server35.hypermart.net/rcschoner/Kitty.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Champion<BR><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0><img src=http://pages.cthome.net/shellene/star.gif height=10 width=11 border=0></span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#6C8361>(4/12/02 8:44:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=483.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EQ Marriages</spa